<P>"What is that?" &s;aid St. Aubert, rou&s;ed again from thought|fulne&s;s. As his ho&s;t repeated his la&s;t &s;entence, a groan e&s;caped from St. Aubert, and then, as if anxious to prevent it from being noticed, he ha&s;tily a&s;ked La Voi&s;in how long he had lived in this neighbourhood. "Almo&s;t from my childhood, &s;ir," replied his ho&s;t.</P>
