<P>EMILY, called, as &s;he had reque&s;ted, at an early hour, awoke, little refre&s;hed by &s;leep, for unea&s;y dreams had pur&s;ued her, and marred the kinde&s;t ble&s;&s;ing of the unhappy. But, when <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> opened her ca&s;ement, looked out upon the woods, bright with the morning &s;un, and in&s;pired the pure air, her mind was &s;ooth|ed. The &s;cene was filled with that cheering fre&s;hne&s;s, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> &s;eems to breathe the very &s;pirit of health, and &s;he heard <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> &s;weet and <HI>picture&s;que</HI> &s;ounds, if &s;uch an expre&s;&s;ion may be allow|ed&mdash;the matin bell of a di&s;tant convent, the faint murmur of the <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">ea-waves, the &s;ong of birds, and the far-off low of cattle, which
