pine branches, while two of Montoni's Venetian &s;ervants follow|ed with lights.</P>
<P>"Your <HI>Excellenza</HI> is welcome to the ca&s;tle," &s;aid the old man, as he rai&s;ed him&s;elf from the hearth, where he had laid the wood: "it has been a lonely place a long while; but you will excu&s;e it, Signor, knowing we had but &s;hort notice. It is near two years, come next fea&s;t of St. Mark, &s;ince your <HI>Excellenza</HI> was within the&s;e walls."</P>
