<P>THE MYSTERIES OF UDOLPHO, A <HI>ROMANCE;</HI> INTERSPERSED WITH SOME PIECES OF POETRY</P>
<P>BY ANN RATCLIFFE, <HI>Author of the Romance of the Fore&s;t, A Sicilian Romance,</HI> &amp;c.</P>
<P>IN THREE VOLUMES. VOL. III.</P>
<Q><L>Fate &s;its on the&s;e dark battlemen's, and frowns,</L>
<L>And, as the portals open to receive.</L>
<L>Her voice, in &s;ullen echoes through the courts,</L>
<L>Tells of a namele&s;s deed.</L></Q>
<P>Bo&s;ton: Printed by <HI>SAMUEL ETHERIDGE,</HI> For J. WHITE, W. SPOTSWOOD, THOMAS <HI>&amp;</HI> ANDREWS, D. WEST, E. LARKIN, W. P. BLAKE, J. WEST, and J. W. FOLSOM. 1795.</P>
</DIV1>
