<P>At length, &s;he found her&s;elf <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">ear the avenue, which, on the <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> of her <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span">, Michael had attempted to pa&s;s in &s;earch of a hou&s;e, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> was &s;till nearly as wild and de&s;olate as it had <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> appeared; for the Count had been &s;o much engaged in directing other improvements, that he had neglected to give orders concerning this exten&s;ive approach, and the road was yet broken, and the trees overloaded with their own luxuriance.</P>
<P>As &s;he &s;tood &s;urveying it, and remembering the emotions which &s;he had <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> &s;uffered there, &s;he &s;uddenly recollected the figure, that had <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> &s;een &s;tealing among the trees, and which
