<P>The man, who was called Jacques, now returned from the <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> gallery. "A fire is lighted there," &s;aid he, "and the birds are dre&s;&s;ing; the table too is &s;pread there, for that place is warmer than this."</P>
<P>His companions approved of the removal, and invited their gue&s;ts to follow to the gallery, of whom Blanche appeared di&s;|tre&s;&s;ed,
